  "market_context": "London session (02:00–05:00 EST) where oil made a low, triggered a change in state of delivery (CISD), then New York session continued higher toward the equilibrium of the prior range and daily fair value gap.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept a prior low during London, closed above the series of down-close candles (CISD), forming a bullish order block that served as a launchpad for NY continuation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified the daily profile structure on the 15-minute chart, noting London session (02:00–05:00 EST) produced a lower low and wick formation.",
    "Step 2: Analyst observed a down-close candle series during London, then a close above those candles—confirming Change in State of Delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 3: Analyst dropped to the 5-minute timeframe at NY open (08:30 EST) to locate the order block formed by the CISD candle and identified a propulsion block upon retest.",
    "Step 4: Analyst placed a long entry at the retest of the order block (propulsion block), stop below the low of the CISD candle, targeting 2R toward the range equilibrium and daily FVG zone.",
    "Step 5: Trade executed successfully: price hit 2R target as NY session continued higher, completing the daily OHLC (open-low-high-close) bullish expansion."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target; successful long entry following London reversal and NY continuation.",
  "lessons": "A valid London reversal requires CISD (close over opposing candles) within the kill zone; NY continuation entries are highest probability when aligned with HTF FVG and range equilibrium targets.",
